PyRogue v0.2.0 Summer 2026 (maybe?) By Andrew Butler
Built with Python 3.14

Work in progress; the goal here is to update PyRogue to better accomdodate OOP beyond basic game elements;
I.e., separate the game engine from the UI, so that UI can be modularized. One of the big shortcomings of 
PyRogue as it exists is that the Tkinter UI is hardcoded into the game, and in general input is not handled
in a very maintainable way. This intends to fix that.

This will lead to pyrogue having an independant game engine package, and a separate package that will act
as the launchable game. This is largely a low-priority rework of PyRogue, so it may take a long time and will
functionally still be mostly the same.

Notes for myself:
